Replace the Coder Getting Started promo with a Composery agent setup card

code-server injects a "Deploy code-server for your team" Coder advert into the
Welcome page (getting-started.diff). This swaps that block's contents for a
"Set up an AI coding agent" card: a grid of agents (logo + name). Each card runs
composery.installAgent (the composery-agents builtin extension) directly via the
command service, which runs that agent's official setup command in a new terminal.
Logos are CSS-masked and filled with the theme accent (textLink.foreground), so
they read as one accent silhouette and adapt to light/dark. Keeps the existing
isEnabledCoderGettingStarted gate, so COMPOSERY_DISABLE_GETTING_STARTED_OVERRIDE
still turns the whole block off.

